title: [Maelstrom Bay, Bottom]
description: A pair of tall elkhorn corals stand in the sand of the bay floor like sentinels.  Bluish turtle grass, thick as a lawn, surrounds the coral.  A few grey, egg-sized stones lay scattered in the turtle grass.  Dozens of yellow-striped fish, no bigger than a dwarf's thumb, meander through the thick grasses.
paths: Obvious exits: north, northeast, east, southeast, south, southwest, west, northwest, up
